Lessons
--------
1. Weak credential hygiene — Default/common passwords enable rapid compromise
2. WordPress administration — Theme editing should be disabled or heavily restricted
3. Leftover credentials — Hardcoded credentials in accessible files are a critical risk
4. Network segmentation failure — Internal services (Jenkins) lack isolation
5. Privilege escalation risk — Services running as root with user-controlled input are game over

